      • cleanState

        protected void cleanState(@NonNull
                          android.os.Bundle sharedBundle)
        Called when fragment should clean its set data.

        This is typically used when user navigates back and data set by part of the program creation should be erased.

        This applies for data saved through validateAndSave(Bundle)

        Default implementation saves nothing. Implementation can only erase data from provided bundle, or doing simple operations, not depending on the fragment state and not modifying fragment state, as the time of this callback is not defined.

        Parameters:
        sharedBundle - bundle to erase the data from
